{{>headerLong}}
    <div class="faqDiv clearfix">
        <div class="questionFAQ">
            <p>How can I make a prediction?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="answerFAQ">
            <p>
                Click on the league you want to predict, and in first place, 
                drag each team to the position you think it will end, 
                then select which players will be the most outstanding this season. 
                Once this is done, click on the button called "Make Prediction".
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faqDiv clearfix">
        <div class="questionFAQ">
            <p>How long can I make a prediction?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="answerFAQ">
            <p>Until RLCS league begins.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faqDiv clearfix">
        <div class="questionFAQ">
            <p>Can I modify a prediction?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="answerFAQ">
            <p>Yes, as long as the RLCS league has not started.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faqDiv clearfix">
        <div class="questionFAQ">
            <p>How can I see my predictions?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="answerFAQ">
            <p>From the same tabs where you made them.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faqDiv clearfix">
        <div class="questionFAQ">
            <p>When will I be able to see the player ranking?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="answerFAQ">
            <p>When the RLCS league has ended.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faqDiv clearfix">
        <div class="questionFAQ">
            <p>How does the point system work?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="answerFAQ">
            <p>
                For each league you will earn: 50 points for each best player you hit, 
                and regarding the final classification, 20 points if you chose the correct position,
                and 10 if the team finished higher or lower than the chosen position.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
{{>footer}}